	 Making Decisions:
	 	Choose between two equally good options
	 	Choose between two equally bad options
	 	Choose whether to take a mixed option of good and bad
	 Deadlines:
	 	automatically add Stress for each period of working under a deadline.
	 		e.g. centuries, decades, years, months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, seconds.
	 		let this go up to the line and there is a lot of Stress to be accumulated
	 Obstacles:
	 	Traffic jams and the like add Stress. Obstacles add Stress when they add required time.
	 Encountering Dissonant Geometries
	 Stepping out of your comfort zone
	 Travel Stress:
	 	Lost Time for other things
	 	Surprises during travel (delays, lost baggage)
	 	Routine Breaking
	 Ambient Stress:
	 	Tension Stress: Gifted by the Plot to Embodiment Characters who aren't doing their job.
	 	Location Stress:
	 		Pollution: Bad air quality (Miasma) adds Stress (we can calculate the Stress from the rolled Score probably)
	 		Noise: Noise (Fury) adds Stress
	 		Crowding: Groups of people automatically add Stress, the bigger the group present and the smaller the space, the more Stress (Dominion and Yonder).
	 		Traffic: Groups of people moving in small spaces and large vehicles will add more Stress (this should be calculated based on Dominion, Yonder and Zeal)
	 		Okay it looks like each Facet of a Location may cause an ambient Stress.
	 			so Facet based Stressors:
		 			Awe: Spiritual Residue / Haunted - ghosts and oppressive airs add stress 
		 			Burden: Debt and Wealth both adds Stress
		 			Craft: Oppressive architecture adds Stress
		 			Dominion: Groups of people add Stress
		 			Enigma: Confusion and getting lost always add Stress
		 			Fury: Noise adds Stress
		 			Gossamer: Draughts and whispers add Stress
		 			Heresy: Discovered lies add Stress (hidden garbage etc)
		 			Inertia: Motion even steady motion adds Stress
		 			Jeer: Humiliation adds Stress. Humour reduces Stress though
		 			Key: Too much information adds stress
		 			Liberty: Generally reduces Stress, but other people's liberty can increase Stress (fear of missing out)
		 			Miasma: Pollution adds Stress
		 			Nature: Groups of animals add Stress
		 			Orthodox: Knowledge adds Stress
		 			Phoenix: Heat adds Stress
		 			Quiet: Thoughts add Stress
		 			Rook: Soaking Damage on Facets adds Stress
		 			Sin: we can say it adds Stress if it makes you feel better...
		 			Trial: Conflict adds Stress
		 			Virtue: Would it make you feel any better to say Virtue doesn't add Stress? 
		 			Wyrd: Doom, and a lack of free will in general, big add Stress
		 			Yonder: Small spaces add Stress, but so can big spaces too sometimes.
		 			Zeal: Acceleration of any sort adds Stress
		 		I guess these should add Stress only if the Stress is greater than their Facet Value (or Boon) (we still need to see about the numbers and how much Stress is good or bad.)

	Stress Management:
		Firstly, we need to say 
		Routine:
			Anything that has become routine for a Character will stress them less (except Hitches). Removing the chance of Shock significantly.

