Thinking about Stress there are a number of ways that it can be used.
1) Stress operates like Value... Small amounts of Stress are meaningless, but huge amounts become terrible. The Boon of the Stress Value would be called Strains / Banes, and the Score would be called Shock / Marks .
	Stress would be gained by card each one adding 2-15 Stress... which is 1-4 Strain and only 1 Shock
	so 2 Stress Cards would be 4-30 Stress 1-7 Strain 1-2 Shock
	3 Cards 6-45 Stress 2-10 Strain 1-3 Shock 
	-- interesting that 3, 10, 45 has a 1d6 Die... That might be useable...
	Characters would be able to store a lot of Stress (over 300) Which I think we limit by adding highest Facet Value to Hitch Value...
	Boon 18 (111) and Bane 16 (92) that's 203... What if we just use Personality Annex or Master Annex that will probably work better. That could work as the amounts are huge with storing 4 Shock being possible.

	This would give certain events plausible big numbers of Stress like the numbers on the table above.

	So here's my first real idea.

	Stress can be Eustress (good Stress that can be used to increase mental and physical activities - see it creates Strain) and Distress (bad stress - stress you can't cope with or that needs working through) you accumulate both.
	When they are added together though you get Strain.
	Strain can become Strain Dice which we can add to a Strain Pool and force a roll (but Strain Dice are not Drama Dice) - Strain Dice could bet Stress on the roll. So if You have 700 Stress you could spend 691 adding a 2d10 Strain Die. This depending upon what is rolled will return 16-4427 Stress? That does not seem right. Instead the Stress bet returns if the Dice roll is below average... 
	
	If Shock was equivalent to Draw and so Stress cards become Shock effects perhaps... Maybe add another level Traumas..

	Hitches will have to be upped as their level of Stress is far too small. Quirks may be Ruins, Flaws Marks and Woes Banes Stress... This lets Stress power Characters which will better than Chi coming from Hitches probably... As Stress will be both good and bad with this system...

	We need to think about how Shock works... 
	A Character has a Stress Limit, but they also have a Strain Limit and a Shock Limit.


	Okay pause that... how else can we model Stress, Strain and Shock

2) The Sway model
	in this model Stress is much like Tao Sway
	Strain could be Facet Sway (stored Stress)
	Shock would be Chi
	Trauma would be Yarn

		Characters gain Stress
		A Character or Descendant can hold as much Stress as their Stress Limit which is their Total Annex Boons.
		Stress after the Stress Limit will cause Shock.
		A Character can burn Stress on Strain Dice that add to the Pool of a Facet or Annex Action, but the rolled die adds Strains equal to the rolled Score. 
			Strains are stored on Annexes or Facets, and can only reach the Facet Boon or the Facet or Annex becomes Strained. 
			Any annex or facet with Strains suffers additional Reaction Time equal to its current Strains.
			Any Strained Annex or Facet can be used, but adds a negative Strain Die to the Pool.
			Strains are healed by rest. Each twenty minutes of rest or sleep will allow a Character to remove a Strain. 
			Strain does not count towards a Character's Stress Limit, but all Stored Strains Reduced add to Shock.
		Shock has different storage limits. Shock is stored on the Master or Personality Annex Score.
		Shock can be burned as GRT, stopping a Character from acting, although they can continue to act, ignoring the Shock until they can store no more.
		
		If a Descendant or Character is filled with Shock then Stress is converted to Strain, all Strain is converted to Shock and all Shock is converted to Trauma.
		Traumas cause long lasting Stress card effects or


Sway Stress Model Take 2
Stress is gained from a variety of sources, but especially Hitches.
Stress can be stored on Annexes, with each Annex able to Store as much Stress as it can generate as a Score, e.g. the Maximum of the Annex Die roll.

Stress can be spent to purchase Strain Dice which can be added to any roll. Typically the Stress spent is treated as a Boon to buy the bonus Strain Die.
Each time you do this it will add a Strain to the Annex. A Strained Annex will have a -1 to all Scores until the Strain has been healed or rested away. 
Typically 1 Point of Strain requires the Character does not use this Annex for a period of time equal to the current Strains as Chi Extend Duration. E.g. A Strain of 1 will add -1 to all rolls and takes only 1 Ordeal Phase to heal, 8 Strains will add -8 and require an entire Scene to pass without using that Annex. 
An Annex can only store Strains equal to the maximum Stress Reduced. 

e.g. Boon 10 *1d6 has Max 6 Stress and 2 Strain

If Stress is full and more Stress is gained, then the Character is Overstressed. Overstressed Characters must convert Stress into Shock Dice.
Stress Reduced + current Strains = Shock Dice (so the Maximum Shock is usually twice the Strains- although extreme Stress can make this more crazy.)

Shock Dice are rolled immediately.
Each Shock Dice is a d6.

1-2: The Shock Die has no Effect
3-4: The Shock Die creates a GRT
5-6: The Shock Die Draws a Stress Card

Characters and Descendants can end up stuck in a whole mess of Shock GRT, or they can end up Drawing cards for the Stress Effects.


